ribing the years she has lived.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\", \"score\": 0.8211810002328083, \"rank\": 0.20546431533204124, \"text\": \"Rose\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\"}, {\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryce_DeWitt\", \"score\": 0.9999996361080528, \"rank\": 1.258567162636586e-07, \"text\": \"DeWitt\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryce_DeWitt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryce_DeWitt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The games kicked off with the opening ceremony on Friday, ahead of most competitions - soccer and rugby already began matches on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Friday's opening ceremony took place along the River Seine instead of being held indoors like many opening ceremonies in past Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials said that there would be a four-mile-long flotilla of nearly 90 boats to carry athletes from more than 200 countries past thousands of spectators.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED STORY |Breakdancing to make Olympic debut at Paris 2024 Games  The NIH's National Institute of Neurological Disorders and Stroke say the cause of Dion's disease is still unknown.\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.